description:
OUTCITE - An integrated platform for comparing reference extraction toolkits and provisioning their output  

 &nbsp; 

  Tobias Backes, Muhammad Ahsan Shahid, Anastasiia Iurshina, Philipp Mayr  

 &nbsp; 

 In this presentation, we show how the  OUTCITE Demonstrator  &lt;https://demo-outcite.gesis.org/&gt; can be used to subjectively and objectively compare different chains of reference extraction tools. 

 &nbsp; 

 Applying pipelines that combine different steps from known reference extraction tools to uploaded PDF documents, we currently provide easy access to GROBID, Cermine, Anystyle, and Exparser. 

 &nbsp; 

 Using different gold and silver datasets, we can objectively compare the performance of different tool combinations. 

 &nbsp; 

 In addition, the intuitive upload functionality allows users to obtain a subjective impression of the different results. In the future, we might be able to provide machine-access to offer users the option to upload multiple PDF files and look up the results later. 

 &nbsp; 

 However, for very large-scale processing, the platform should be installed locally by users seeking to run it on thousands of PDFs. 

 &nbsp; 

 Developers of reference extraction tools are invited to provide their code either as standalone executables or as Python modules so that they can be integrated as additional pipeline options. 

 &nbsp;

